<TITLE> BNP calls for stand against 'plots' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 25 (bdnews24.com) - BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain called upon all nationalist forces to stand united to resist the plot to make the country dysfunctional. "There is a plot today to cripple the country's independence and to make the country dysfunctional," he said, addressing a discussion at the Institution of Engineers, Bangladesh. Calling on 'nationalist forces' to face the challenge, he said, "There is no alternative way if this plot is to be resisted." On last month's BDR mutiny, he said, "Those who can reap benefits if our border force is affected have caused this incident." "The people want to know who they are," he said. b
